WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.667 --> 00:00:04.167
♪♪

00:00:04.167 --> 00:00:05.434
Narrator: IN ORDER TO ANSWER

00:00:05.434 --> 00:00:07.367
THE AGE-OLD MOVIE MYTH THAT...
[ WILHELM SCREAM ]

00:00:07.367 --> 00:00:09.200
[baritone] "IN SPACE,

00:00:09.200 --> 00:00:12.767
NOBODY CAN HEAR YOU
SCREAM."

00:00:12.767 --> 00:00:14.534
...ALLIE, RACHEL, AND CANNAN...

00:00:14.534 --> 00:00:18.100
25 INCHES OF MERCURY
AT 51 dB.

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:19.601
Allie: COOL.

00:00:19.601 --> 00:00:21.434
...ARE WAITING FOR THEIR
VACUUM CHAMBER

00:00:21.434 --> 00:00:25.000
TO HIT 29.92 INCHES OF MERCURY.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:27.667
AND IT'S TAKING AWHILE.

00:00:27.667 --> 00:00:29.667
I COULD FALL ASLEEP.

00:00:29.667 --> 00:00:31.133
PATIENCE, MY PADAWAN.

00:00:31.133 --> 00:00:32.200
I DON'T HAVE PATIENCE.

00:00:32.200 --> 00:00:34.200
-[LAUGHS]
-IT'S ONE OF MY TALENTS.

00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:36.501
Narrator:
THE FINAL FEW INCHES
TAKE THE LONGEST

00:00:36.501 --> 00:00:39.367
BECAUSE THE PRESSURE
DECREASES EXPONENTIALLY.

00:00:39.367 --> 00:00:41.300
[Helium pitch]
GO AWAY.

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:43.200
AAAAAAAAAAAH!

00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:45.467
FROM THE LAST READING...

00:00:45.467 --> 00:00:48.133
28 INCHES OF MERCURY.

00:00:48.133 --> 00:00:51.667
...UNTIL THE VACUUM IS AS CLOSE
TO PERFECT AS THEY CAN GET,

00:00:51.667 --> 00:00:54.934
CAPTAIN RASPBERRY HAS ASCENDED
FROM THE PEAK OF EVEREST

00:00:54.934 --> 00:00:58.434
TO APPROXIMATELY
18 MILES ABOVE SEA LEVEL.

00:00:58.434 --> 00:00:59.667
[ POIGNANT TUNE PLAYS ]

00:00:59.667 --> 00:01:02.567
IT'S AS CLOSE TO SPACE
AS HE'S EVER GONNA GET.

00:01:02.567 --> 00:01:04.067
SO, THIS IS IT.

00:01:04.067 --> 00:01:05.968
IS HIS SCREAM INAUDIBLE?

00:01:05.968 --> 00:01:07.267
[ GENTLE INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC ]

00:01:07.267 --> 00:01:10.434
ALRIGHT!
WE'RE AT A FULL VACUUM.

00:01:10.434 --> 00:01:14.534
FOR 30 INCHES OF MERCURY,
THAT IS 49 DECIBELS.

00:01:14.534 --> 00:01:17.534
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

00:01:17.534 --> 00:01:19.567
Allie:
STILL SEEMS KINDA LOUD.

00:01:19.567 --> 00:01:21.234
WELL, THE WHOOPEE CUSHION
ISN'T MOVING ANYMORE

00:01:21.234 --> 00:01:23.033
AND THERE'S NO AIR
IN THE CHAMBER.

00:01:23.033 --> 00:01:24.868
THE SOUND HAS TO BE
COMING FROM SOMEWHERE.

00:01:24.868 --> 00:01:26.834
YEAH, THAT'S WEIRD,
ISN'T IT?

00:01:26.834 --> 00:01:28.400
♪♪

00:01:28.400 --> 00:01:30.601
[ WHISPERING WHOOSH ]

00:01:30.601 --> 00:01:32.300
YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS?

00:01:32.300 --> 00:01:35.100
IT'S THE MOTOR.
I CAN FEEL IT VIBRATING

00:01:35.100 --> 00:01:38.901
AND HITCHING
UNDER MY FINGERS.

00:01:38.901 --> 00:01:41.634
OUR MICROPHONE IS PICKING UP
MORE THAN JUST A SCREAM.

00:01:41.634 --> 00:01:43.767
THERE ARE TWO SPIKES,
THE SOUND OF THE SCREAM

00:01:43.767 --> 00:01:46.868
AND THE SOUND OF THE MOTOR, AND,
WHEN WE'RE AT A FULL VACUUM,

00:01:46.868 --> 00:01:50.000
THE SOUND OF THE SCREAM
GOES AWAY.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:52.834
Narrator:
YEP, THERE IS NO SCREAM
IN THE VACUUM CHAMBER.

00:01:52.834 --> 00:01:54.934
THE ONLY NOISE
PICKED UP BY THE MIC

00:01:54.934 --> 00:01:56.434
IS THE VIBRATION OF THE MOTOR,

00:01:56.434 --> 00:01:59.934
WHERE IT'S MAKING CONTACT
WITH THE CHAMBER'S WALL.

00:01:59.934 --> 00:02:02.100
THERE'S DEFINITELY NOT
A SCREAM IN THAT CHAMBER.

00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:05.767
-NO.
-SO, HAVE WE ANSWERED IT?

00:02:05.767 --> 00:02:06.934
GOOD QUESTION.

00:02:06.934 --> 00:02:08.434
[ HARMONICA PLAYS
LACONIC TUNE ]

00:02:08.434 --> 00:02:12.167
CAPTAIN RASPBERRY HAS NOW TAKEN
HIS MAIDEN VOYAGE INTO SPACE.

00:02:12.167 --> 00:02:15.767
[ "THE BLUE DANUBE" PLAYS ]
[ FARTING ]

00:02:15.767 --> 00:02:18.000
HE WAS ABLE
TO CONTINUE SCREAMING

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:19.567
UNTIL WE HAD PULLED
THE FULL VACUUM

00:02:19.567 --> 00:02:21.167
AND, THEN, HIS VOCAL CORDS
ARE NOT MOVING,

00:02:21.167 --> 00:02:25.834
THERE WAS NO AIR IN THE SYSTEM
AND IT WAS PRETTY AMAZING.

00:02:25.834 --> 00:02:28.067
IT'S A PRETTY GOOD TEST,
IN MY OPINION.

00:02:28.067 --> 00:02:29.467
Narrator:
MYTH CONFIRMED, RIGHT?

00:02:29.467 --> 00:02:32.534
NO AIR EQUALS NO SCREAM.

00:02:32.534 --> 00:02:34.834
WELL, NOT SO FAST.

00:02:34.834 --> 00:02:38.667
TEAM SCREAM HAS ONE LAST
SCENARIO THEY WANT TO TEST.

00:02:38.667 --> 00:02:40.367
ONE LAST BREATH.

00:02:40.367 --> 00:02:43.634
[ OUTRO PLAYS ]

00:02:43.634 --> 00:02:44.868
THIS IS OUR LAST BREATH.

00:02:44.868 --> 00:02:47.400
[ PULSING HISSES ]

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:49.968
THIS IS AS IF YOU WERE THRUST
OUT OF THE AIR LOCK AND ONLY

00:02:49.968 --> 00:02:52.400
HAVE WHAT AIR YOU WERE ABLE
TO SAVE IN YOUR LUNGS.

00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:53.400
ONE.

00:02:53.400 --> 00:02:56.067
[ FARTING ]

00:02:56.067 --> 00:02:59.367
[ LAUGHING ]

00:02:59.367 --> 00:03:02.667
OUR LUNG IS PLAYED
BY THIS BICYCLE INNER TUBE.

00:03:02.667 --> 00:03:05.467
ONCE FILLED WITH AIR
AND UNDER A FULL VACUUM,

00:03:05.467 --> 00:03:07.133
THE BREATH WILL BE RELEASED.

00:03:07.133 --> 00:03:09.067
♪♪

00:03:09.067 --> 00:03:10.367
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

00:03:10.367 --> 00:03:11.367
[laughing]
DID YOU GET IT?

00:03:11.367 --> 00:03:12.968
-YAH, I GOT IT.
-OKAY.

00:03:12.968 --> 00:03:15.167
SEND THAT TO THE --
WOW, THAT'S TERRIFYING.

00:03:15.167 --> 00:03:16.801
IT SHOULD ANSWER THE QUESTION

00:03:16.801 --> 00:03:19.000
WHETHER, "IN SPACE,
NO ONE CAN HEAR YOU SCREAM."

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:20.801
[ BLOWING RASPBERRY ]

00:03:20.801 --> 00:03:22.767
Narrator: TEAM SCREAM
HAS ALREADY PROVEN THAT,

00:03:22.767 --> 00:03:24.701
WITH NO MEDIUM TO CARRY SOUND...

00:03:24.701 --> 00:03:26.601
IT'S LIKE
A NEW INSTRUMENT.

00:03:26.601 --> 00:03:28.701
...THERE IS NO SOUND.

00:03:28.701 --> 00:03:29.767
HERE WE GO.

00:03:29.767 --> 00:03:30.834
♪♪

00:03:30.834 --> 00:03:32.067
[ FARTING ]

00:03:32.067 --> 00:03:33.667
[ LAUGHS ]
ALRIGHT.

00:03:33.667 --> 00:03:34.868
LET'S VACUUM
THIS PUPPY UP.

00:03:34.868 --> 00:03:36.267
I THINK WE'RE READY
TO TURN THIS ON.

00:03:36.267 --> 00:03:37.868
[ FUNK PLAYS ]

00:03:37.868 --> 00:03:40.868
THE PREVIOUS TEST REMOVED
ALL THE AIR FROM THE SYSTEM...

00:03:40.868 --> 00:03:44.067
Rachel:
ALRIGHT, WE'RE GOING ON
TO 10 INCHES OF MERCURY.

00:03:44.067 --> 00:03:46.567
...AND THE RESULT WAS
AS EXPECTED,

00:03:46.567 --> 00:03:49.100
BUT, THIS TIME,
THE UNLUCKY ASTRONAUT...

00:03:49.100 --> 00:03:51.868
ADAM LOOKS VERY HAPPY,
FLOATING AROUND IN SPACE.

00:03:51.868 --> 00:03:53.400
...IS JETTISONED INTO SPACE

00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:56.234
WHILE HOLDING ONE
LAST LUNGFUL OF AIR.

00:03:56.234 --> 00:03:57.300
Cannan:
ARE WE THERE YET?

00:03:57.300 --> 00:03:58.667
HEY, MAN,
DON'T TRY THAT.

00:03:58.667 --> 00:04:00.100
I WILL TURN THIS CAR
[laughing] RIGHT AROUND.

00:04:00.100 --> 00:04:01.901
[ LAUGHING ]

00:04:01.901 --> 00:04:03.701
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

00:04:03.701 --> 00:04:05.000
TO SIMULATE THAT,

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:07.400
THE TEAM WILL BRING
THE CHAMBER TO A VACUUM,

00:04:07.400 --> 00:04:10.033
WITH THAT ONE
LAST BREATH INTACT,

00:04:10.033 --> 00:04:11.634
AND THEN LET HIM SCREAM.

00:04:11.634 --> 00:04:14.400
♪♪

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:16.234
WE ARE AT 29.5.

00:04:16.234 --> 00:04:17.767
THIS IS PERFECT.

00:04:17.767 --> 00:04:19.234
MY EXPERIMENTAL
[laughing] ASTRONAUT

00:04:19.234 --> 00:04:20.801
IS HOLDING
HIS LAST BREATH.

00:04:20.801 --> 00:04:22.000
ALLIE, YOU WANNA
CALL IT IN?

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:23.467
YEAH.
ALRIGHT.

00:04:23.467 --> 00:04:24.834
HEY, CANNAN,
ARE YOU READY?

00:04:24.834 --> 00:04:27.400
I'M READY.
RECORDING.

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:30.667
ALRIGHT, THIS IS
LAST BREATH IN SPACE,

00:04:30.667 --> 00:04:33.167
ADAM WHOOPEE CUSHION TEST,

00:04:33.167 --> 00:04:34.501
IN THREE!

00:04:34.501 --> 00:04:35.834
TWO!

00:04:35.834 --> 00:04:37.133
ONE!

00:04:37.133 --> 00:04:38.934
[ RATTLING ]

00:04:41.334 --> 00:04:42.501
-LET'S GO CHECK IT OUT.
-OKAY.

00:04:42.501 --> 00:04:44.133
Narrator: IF ADAM'S
LAST BREATH WAS AUDIBLE,

00:04:44.133 --> 00:04:47.033
IT WAS SO FAINT
THE TEAM MISSED IT.

00:04:47.033 --> 00:04:49.868
BUT THE VIBRATION OF THE WHOOPEE
CUSHION LOOKED PROMISING.

00:04:49.868 --> 00:04:51.701
WHAT DID THE MIC PICK UP?

00:04:51.701 --> 00:04:53.033
ALRIGHT, CANNAN,
WHAT DID YOU GET?

00:04:53.033 --> 00:04:55.033
Allie:
IN THREE!

00:04:55.033 --> 00:04:56.033
TWO!

00:04:56.033 --> 00:04:57.033
ONE!

00:04:57.033 --> 00:05:00.501
[ FARTING ]

00:05:00.501 --> 00:05:01.901
THAT'S A SOUND!

00:05:01.901 --> 00:05:05.067
[ POIGNANT TUNE PLAYS ]
[ FARTING ]

00:05:05.067 --> 00:05:06.834
THAT ACTUALLY
SOUNDS LIKE A FART.

00:05:06.834 --> 00:05:08.601
LIKE A LAST,
DYING FART IN SPACE.

00:05:08.601 --> 00:05:10.367
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:05:10.367 --> 00:05:12.567
[ FARTING ]

00:05:12.567 --> 00:05:13.634
THAT'S A RESULT!

00:05:13.634 --> 00:05:14.667
WELL DONE!

00:05:14.667 --> 00:05:17.400
[ ANGELIC CHORALE PLAYS ]
[ FARTING ]

00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:19.033
-THANK YOU.
-OUTSTANDING.

00:05:19.033 --> 00:05:20.033
Allie: ONE!

00:05:20.033 --> 00:05:24.400
[ FARTING ]

00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:26.467
HOW IS IT POSSIBLE TO HEAR
MY LAST, DYING SCREAM

00:05:26.467 --> 00:05:27.934
INSIDE THIS VACUUM CHAMBER?

00:05:27.934 --> 00:05:32.534
WELL, QUITE SIMPLY BECAUSE THE
AIR BEING EXHALED BY MY LUNGS

00:05:32.534 --> 00:05:34.801
IS PROVIDING A MEDIUM
FOR THAT SOUND

00:05:34.801 --> 00:05:37.100
TO TRAVEL TO THE OUTSIDE
OF THE CHAMBER.

00:05:37.100 --> 00:05:38.968
"OH, BUT WAIT A MINUTE!"
I HEAR YOU COMPLAINING.

00:05:38.968 --> 00:05:41.834
"THAT'S NOT ACCURATE
TO THE VACUUM OF SPACE!"

00:05:41.834 --> 00:05:46.367
AND I WOULD AGREE, EXCEPT
UNDER THIS ONE, SPECIFIC CASE.

00:05:46.367 --> 00:05:48.133
THAT IS, IMAGINE YOU'RE
IN A SPACE SUIT,

00:05:48.133 --> 00:05:49.634
HOLDING ONTO SOMEONE WHO ISN'T,

00:05:49.634 --> 00:05:53.234
AND THEY EXHALE THEIR LAST
BREATH TO SCREAM AT YOU.

00:05:53.234 --> 00:05:56.434
I WOULD SUBMIT THAT
THEIR BREATH WOULD CARRY,

00:05:56.434 --> 00:05:58.267
MAYBE JUST ACROSS
A FOOT OF SPACE,

00:05:58.267 --> 00:06:01.033
THE SOUND OF THEIR SCREAM
INTO YOUR HELMET.

00:06:01.033 --> 00:06:04.067
THAT'S A RESULT
I WILL STAND BEHIND.

00:06:04.067 --> 00:06:05.667
[ FARTING ]

00:06:05.667 --> 00:06:07.868
ALRIGHT, GUYS, THAT MYTH
YOU HAVE BEEN TESTING IS THAT

00:06:07.868 --> 00:06:11.234
[hoarsely] "IN SPACE,
NO ONE CAN HEAR YOU SCREAM."

00:06:11.234 --> 00:06:12.367
I DON'T KNOW WHY I'M
TALKING LIKE THAT.

00:06:12.367 --> 00:06:13.367
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:06:13.367 --> 00:06:15.167
BUSTED, PLAUSIBLE,
OR CONFIRMED?

00:06:15.167 --> 00:06:16.968
WE FOUND THE EXCEPTION:
THAT, AS LONG AS YOU'RE

00:06:16.968 --> 00:06:18.167
WITHIN A FOOT
OF THE PERSON

00:06:18.167 --> 00:06:19.968
WHO'S SCREAMING,
YOU CAN STILL HEAR THEM.

00:06:19.968 --> 00:06:21.200
THAT WOULD MEAN
IT'S BUSTED.

00:06:21.200 --> 00:06:22.434
-BUSTED.
-BUSTED.

00:06:22.434 --> 00:06:24.834
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]
AAAAAAAAAAAH!

00:06:24.834 --> 00:06:26.300
[ SUSPENSEFUL
CHORD STRIKES ]

